# Excel-Sales-Analytics

**Project 1: P&L Analysis Dashboard** 

https://github.com/areebbaigwork/Excel-Sales-Analytics/blob/main/p_and_l_.pdf

This project focuses on building a clean Profit & Loss view to understand how the business has grown over time and where the money is actually being made.

Using the dataset, I analyzed performance across multiple years and broke it down into key financial components like Net Sales, COGS, and Gross Margin.

From the data  one thing that stood out immediately was the sharp growth:

Net Sales jumped from 87.5M (2019) to 598.9M (2021)
But at the same time, Gross Margin % dropped slightly (~41% → 36%)

So while revenue scaled aggressively, profitability efficiency didn’t improve at the same pace — which is a pretty realistic business scenario.



What I worked on in this project:

Built P&L structure from raw data
Created year-over-year comparisons
Analyzed margin trends vs revenue growth
Looked at monthly patterns to check consistency





**Project 2: Sales & Market Performance Analysis**

https://github.com/areebbaigwork/Excel-Sales-Analytics/blob/main/sales_market_report.pdf

In this project, I focused more on who and where the revenue is coming from.

From the customer-level data , I analyzed which customers are driving growth and how their contribution has changed over time.

Some interesting observations:

Platforms like Amazon (82.1M) and Atliq Exclusive (61.1M) became major contributors by 2021
Many smaller customers showed extremely high growth %, but from a low base (so not always impactful in absolute terms)
Overall sales grew ~3x, but growth wasn’t evenly distributed across customers

I also looked at country-level performance vs targets:

Most regions missed their targets slightly (~8–12% below)
Big markets like USA, India, and Canada contributed heavily but still underperformed targets
This suggests either overly aggressive targets or operational inefficiencies

What I worked on in this project:

Customer-level revenue analysis
Identifying top contributors vs high-growth low-base customers
Market-wise performance vs targets
Highlighting gaps between actuals and expectations
